President Barack Obama has announced his intention to nominate Ron Sims, County Executive of King County, Washington, as the Deputy Secretary at the U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD). Sims, who has earned a national reputation for his environmental stewardship and government reforms, will be responsible for managing HUD's day-to-day operations, budget, and employees. He has been praised for his innovative leadership and collaborative problem-solving approach. Sims, who oversees the 13th most populous county in the nation, has a background in urban government and extensive experience in various organizations. His nomination requires Senate approval. HUD is committed to sustaining homeownership, creating affordable housing, and supporting vulnerable populations.